00:00:13.075 --> 00:00:17.760
Lavanya, what will you be making?
Paneer Shahi Korma

00:00:34.001 --> 00:00:36.112
Ingredients required to make Paneer Shahi Korma

00:00:36.490 --> 00:00:42.643
Paneer (Cottage Cheese), Onion Paste, Green Chillies, Garam Masala, Ginger Garlic Paste,

00:00:42.849 --> 00:00:48.928
 Turmeric, Cashews &amp; Poppy Seeds Paste, Coriander, Chilli Powder, Salt, Oil

00:00:57.549 --> 00:01:02.178
Take a pan and heat some oil for deep frying

00:01:03.195 --> 00:01:08.307
Fry the paneer cubes

00:01:23.063 --> 00:01:27.369
Add just a little salt to the paneer 
to avoid it from sticking to the pan

00:01:38.787 --> 00:01:42.656
Keep the fried paneer aside

00:01:51.243 --> 00:01:56.151
Grind two onions into a paste

00:02:02.849 --> 00:02:06.261
Fry the paste and two chopped green chillies

00:02:11.624 --> 00:02:15.395
Add some salt

00:02:17.417 --> 00:02:29.521
Add some turmeric powder and some garam masala

00:02:34.410 --> 00:02:39.638
Add some ginger garlic paste

00:02:48.609 --> 00:02:57.000
Grind some equal quantities of cashews &amp; poppy seeds into a paste

00:03:00.475 --> 00:03:06.159
Add the paste into the pan

00:03:37.685 --> 00:03:41.265
Add some red chilli powder

00:04:08.362 --> 00:04:13.463
Add some fresh grated cottage cheese (paneer)

00:04:15.563 --> 00:04:21.602
Now, add the fried cottage cheese (paneer)

00:04:26.690 --> 00:04:30.978
Add half a cup of water

00:04:39.579 --> 00:04:44.492
Let it cook for another 2-5 mins

00:04:46.681 --> 00:04:52.722
Close the lid

00:05:08.330 --> 00:05:11.924
The oil rising up is a sign that the dish is cooked

00:05:14.047 --> 00:05:18.917
Add some coriander

00:05:24.235 --> 00:05:32.452
Take it into a serving bowl and garnish with vegetables of your choice

